    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-carbonara-style-bacon-and-gochujang-udon/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat and boil a kettle</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to crisp</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-carbonara-style-bacon-and-gochujang-udon/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>udon noodles</strong> to a large bowl, cover them with <strong>boiled water </strong>then set aside to soak for 4-5 min</p><p>Tip: Gently separate the noodles with a fork!</p><p>Drain the <strong>soaked noodles</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic </strong>then trim and slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-carbonara-style-bacon-and-gochujang-udon/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the bacon is starting to crisp, add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-carbonara-style-bacon-and-gochujang-udon/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>gochujang paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-carbonara-style-bacon-and-gochujang-udon/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> drained noodles </strong>and your <strong>blanched</strong> <strong>peas </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-carbonara-style-bacon-and-gochujang-udon/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once warmed through,<strong> </strong>add your <strong>double</strong> <strong>cream</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a very generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy carbonara-style bacon & gochujang udon</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-carbonara-style-bacon-and-gochujang-udon/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy carbonara-style bacon & gochujang udon</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>,<strong> </strong>your<strong> toasted sesame seeds</strong> and the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
